article.headline: W. Michigan 74, Ball St. 61
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. (AP) -- Derek Fracalossi scored a career-high 19 points and all of Western Michigan's starters scored in double figures in a 74-61 victory Tuesday night over Ball State. The Broncos (6-9, 1-1 Mid-American) hit 68.2 percent of their shots in the second half to erase a seven-point deficit and win their fifth consecutive home game. Skip Mills scored 24 points for Ball State (4-11, 0-2), but had just four in the second half. He hit 7-of-10 shots in the first half as the Cardinals raced to a 31-27 lead. A 12-2 run put the Broncos ahead 46-41 with 11:51 left, and Ball State got no closer than two points after that. Mills scored 17 points in the first 10 minutes and was the only Ball State player to score until Jarelle Redden hit a shot with 9:35 left in the first half. David Kool added 15 points for Western Michigan. Michael Redell and Shawntes Gary each scored 12 and Joe Reitz had 10. Kool hit all four of his free throws, stretching his streak to 29 consecutive made free throws in his freshman season -- the second-longest streak in school history and eight behind a record that has stood for more than 40 years. D'Andre Peyton added 12 points for Ball State, which lost its fifth consecutive game.
